definition.value: The determination of the amount of prorubricytes present in a sample. [ NCI ]
The determination of the amount of rubricytes present in a sample. [ NCI ]

label.value: Segmented Neutrophils to Neutrophils Ratio Measurement

definition.value: The determination of the ratio of segmented neutrophils compared to neutrophils present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage. [NCI ]
The determination of the ratio of immature reticulocytes to total reticulocytes present in a sample. [ NCI ]

label.value: standard deviation of the normal-to-normal inter beat intervals

definition.value: Quantification of the intervals between normal heartbeats, expressed as standard deviation.

label.value: root mean square of the successive differences of inter beat intervals

definition.value: Quantification of the differences in intervals between heartbeats, expressed as root mean square.

label.value: peak-valley respiratory sinus arrhythmia or high frequency power

definition.value: Quantification of some aspects of sinus arrhythmia or high frequency power.
Quantification of symptom associated with nicotine dependence.
Quantification of symptom associated with nicotine withdrawal.
Quantification of the maximum number of cigarettes that a subject smoked per day

label.value: nausea and vomiting of pregnancy severity measurement

Quantification of the levels of ADAMTS13 protein in a sample, typically blood plasma
Quantification of the mineral density of the heel bone

label.value: Epstein Barr virus nuclear antigen-1 seropositivity

definition.value: The result of a measurement of circulating Epstein Barr virus nuclear antigen-1 antibodies used in the diagnosis of latent Epstein-Barr virus infection

label.value: Epstein Barr viral capsid antigen seropositivity

label.value: Epstein Barr viral capsid antigen IgG measurement

definition.value: Quantification of antibodies to the Epstein-Barr virus viral capsid antigen, typically in serum.

Quantification of any aspect of the morphology of the cranial vault, including shape, size, structure or pattern. The cranial vault is a region comprising interlocking flat bones surrounding the cerebral cortex.
Quantification of the thickness of the choroid, the vascular layer of the eye lying between the retina and the sclera.
A quantitative measurement of the amount of sodium present in a sample.
A quantitative measurement of the amount of potassium present in a sample.
A quantitative measurement of the amount of chloride present in a sample.
A calculated measurement corresponding to the ratio or percent reduction in heart chamber diameter between end-systole and end-diastole.
A calculated measurement of heart wall geometry.  It represents a measure of the wall thickness normalized to the size of the chamber lumen.
A quantitative measurement of the thickness of an interventricular septum.
A quantitative measurement of the thickness or depth of the dorsal/posterior wall of the heart.
A quantitative measure calculated as the difference between the epicardium delimited volume and the left ventricular chamber volume
The left ventricular mass divided by the subject's body surface area

The E/A ratio is a marker of the function of the left ventricle of the heart. It represents the ratio of peak velocity blood flow from gravity in early diastole (the E wave) to peak velocity flow in late diastole caused by atrial contraction (the A wave).
Quantification of levels of fructosamine present in a sample.
Quantification of the percentage of serum albumin in a sample that is glycated.
Quantification of the total amount of glycated albumin in a sample.
Quantification of the total amount of atazanavir, typically assayed in hair. This is used as a measure of exposure to the drug.
The determination of the amount of glycated albumin related peptide present in a biological specimen.
Quantification of the amount of proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 in plasma.

Quantification of alpha synuclein levels in the cerebrospinal fluid.
Quantification of the presence of absence of the APOL1 risk genotype in an individual
Quantification of any aspect of growth of the basal ganglia during development
Quantification of any aspect of the growth of the brain during development
Quantification of any aspect of the growth of the cerebellum during development
Quantification of any aspect of growth of the cerebral cortex during development

Quantification of some aspect of erosive tooth wear. Erosive tooth wear is a condition where non-bacterial acids dissolve and soften the tooth surface, thus exposing the tooth to mechanical forces.

Quantification of executive function in an individual, for example using the Behavioural Rating Inventory of Executive Function (BRIEF). Tests of executive function may be performed as part of a more comprehensive assessment to diagnose neurological and psychiatric disorders.
